title: Six children in the Bay Area rescued in nationwide human-trafficking sting
text:
Photo: Kale Williams Special Agent David J. Johnson, head of the FBI's San Francisco office, announces Thursday that six children were rescued in the Bay Area as part of a nationwide sting on human trafficking. Special Agent David J. Johnson, head of the FBI's San Francisco...
A nationwide human trafficking sting led to the rescue of six children in the Bay Area who were forced into prostitution and the arrests of eight suspects accused of pimping them out, authorities announced Thursday.
